init_text: Your entire life, you've been told you're deathly allergic to bees. You've always had people protecting you from them, be it your mother or a hired hand. Today, one slips through and lands on your shoulder. You hear a tiny voice say "Your Majesty, what are your orders?"

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You start to panic and scream.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The wings are dark brown with yellow stripes.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You can't control them and you flail about.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: the bee on your shoulder chirps.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You flail about some more and feel a sharp pain on your back.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You turn around and see a pair of stingers, like those of a bee, sticking out your back.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You feel a tickle on your face and start flailing again.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You see your hands, which have gained a kind of bee-pollen fuzz.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You look at your chest and you start to see a faint black-and-yellow striped pattern.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You look down at your feet and see that they've turned into bee's feet, complete with the two little hooks for climbing.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "You are queen of the bees, and you will live out your days here in this hive.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "You will live here with your subjects, and you will never be alone."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: A doctor yells into your face, "Stay with me, ma'am!
